  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The general objective of the study is to investigate the effects of the daily consumption of
      spices and herbs for four (4) consecutive weeks in endothelial function and cardiovascular
      risk factors of men and postmenopausal women.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose is to assess whether the polyphenol/antioxidant content of different spices will
      affect endothelial function and other cardiovascular risk factors.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
